SUMMARY:Echoes of a Golden Empire
DESCRIPTION:The Vijayanagara Empire redefined the political\, cultural and literary scene of South India\, “an epoch of transition from the Old to the New” – as historian Robert Sewell puts it. This period saw some of the most prolific thinkers\, writers and musicians who moved the cultural narrative ahead by eons\, as compared to any other time in Indian history. \nIn this multi-sensorial performance\, we intend to musically traverse through some of the highs of this Golden Era and explore how they are still relevant to this day – when our linguistic and socio-cultural identities are constantly attacked. \nSupported by: \n \n
