SUMMARY:Wedding Album
DESCRIPTION:Girish Karnad’s Wedding Album is a poignant and humorous exploration of the modern Indian family\, set against the backdrop of an arranged marriage. Through the lives of an upper-middle-class family preparing for their daughter’s wedding\, the play delves into the contradictions between tradition and modernity\, love and duty\, appearance and reality. \nWith razor-sharp dialogue and layered storytelling\, Wedding Album offers a deeply relatable and thought-provoking look at family bonds\, generational conflicts\, and personal aspirations in contemporary India. \nCredits:\nDirected by Kishore Acharya\nProduced by Courtyard Koota \nCast:\nReshmi Nair\nK T Thomas\nChaithra Ballal\nLakshmi Karanth\nAaria Madhup\nHarish Seshadri\nBharathi Govindasamy\nGopikrishna P Y\nMili Sudhakar\nVikram Balakrishna\nSrinidhi Achar\nNikhil Bharadwaj \nIn collaboration with:\n \n
